    {
      "segments": [
        {
          "scid": "sn12.28:1.1",
          "pli": "Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati. ",
          "en": "At Sāvatthī. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn12.28:1.2",
          "pli": "“Tatra kho … pe … ",
          "en": " "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn12.28:1.3",
          "pli": "idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu jarāmaraṇaṃ pajānāti, jarāmaraṇasamudayaṃ pajānāti, jarāmaraṇanirodhaṃ pajānāti, jarāmaraṇanirodhagāminiṃ paṭipadaṃ pajānāti, jātiṃ pajānāti … pe … ",
          "en": "“A mendicant understands old age and death, their origin, their cessation, and the practice that leads to their cessation. They understand rebirth … "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn12.28:1.4",
          "pli": "bhavaṃ pajānāti … ",
          "en": "continued existence … "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn12.28:1.5",
          "pli": "upādānaṃ pajānāti … ",
          "en": "grasping … "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn12.28:1.6",
          "pli": "taṇhaṃ pajānāti … ",
          "en": "craving … "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn12.28:1.7",
          "pli": "vedanaṃ pajānāti … ",
          "en": "feeling … "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn12.28:1.8",
          "pli": "phassaṃ pajānāti … ",
          "en": "contact … "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn12.28:1.9",
          "pli": "saḷāyatanaṃ pajānāti … ",
          "en": "the six sense fields … "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn12.28:1.10",
          "pli": "nāmarūpaṃ pajānāti … ",
          "en": "name and form … "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn12.28:1.11",
          "pli": "viññāṇaṃ pajānāti … ",
          "en": "consciousness … "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn12.28:1.12",
          "pli": "saṅkhāre pajānāti, saṅkhārasamudayaṃ pajānāti, saṅkhāranirodhaṃ pajānāti, saṅkhāranirodhagāminiṃ paṭipadaṃ pajānāti. ",
          "en": "They understand choices, their origin, their cessation, and the practice that leads to their cessation. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn12.28:2.1",
          "pli": "Katamañca, bhikkhave, jarāmaraṇaṃ? ",
          "en": "And what is old age and death? "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn12.28:2.2",
          "pli": "Yā tesaṃ tesaṃ sattānaṃ tamhi tamhi sattanikāye jarā jīraṇatā khaṇḍiccaṃ pāliccaṃ valittacatā āyuno saṃhāni indriyānaṃ paripāko—",
          "en": "The old age, decrepitude, broken teeth, grey hair, wrinkly skin, diminished vitality, and failing faculties of the various sentient beings in the various orders of sentient beings. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn12.28:2.3",
          "pli": "ayaṃ vuccati jarā. ",
          "en": "This is called old age. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn12.28:2.4",
          "pli": "Yā tesaṃ tesaṃ sattānaṃ tamhā tamhā sattanikāyā cuti cavanatā bhedo antaradhānaṃ maccu maraṇaṃ kālakiriyā khandhānaṃ bhedo kaḷevarassa nikkhepo; ",
          "en": "The passing away, perishing, disintegration, demise, mortality, death, decease, breaking up of the aggregates, and laying to rest of the corpse of the various sentient beings in the various orders of sentient beings. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn12.28:2.5",
          "pli": "idaṃ vuccati maraṇaṃ. ",
          "en": "This is called death. … "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn12.28:2.6",
          "pli": "Iti ayañca jarā idañca maraṇaṃ. ",
          "en": "Such is old age, and such is death. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn12.28:2.7",
          "pli": "Idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, jarāmaraṇaṃ. ",
          "en": "This is called old age and death. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn12.28:2.8",
          "pli": "Jātisamudayā jarāmaraṇasamudayo; ",
          "en": "Rebirth is the origin of old age and death. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn12.28:2.9",
          "pli": "jātinirodhā jarāmaraṇanirodho. ",
          "en": "When rebirth ceases, old age and death cease. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn12.28:2.10",
          "pli": "Ayameva ariyo aṭṭhaṅgiko maggo jarāmaraṇanirodhagāminī paṭipadā. ",
          "en": "The practice that leads to the cessation of old age and death is simply this noble eightfold path, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn12.28:2.11",
          "pli": "Seyyathidaṃ—sammādiṭṭhi … pe … sammāsamādhi. ",
          "en": "that is: right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, right effort, right mindfulness, and right immersion. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn12.28:3.1",
          "pli": "Katamā ca, bhikkhave, jāti … pe … ",
          "en": "And what is rebirth? … "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn12.28:3.2",
          "pli": "katamo ca, bhikkhave, bhavo … ",
          "en": "And what is continued existence? … "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn12.28:3.3",
          "pli": "katamañca, bhikkhave, upādānaṃ … ",
          "en": "And what is grasping? … "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn12.28:3.4",
          "pli": "katamā ca, bhikkhave, taṇhā … ",
          "en": "And what is craving? … "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn12.28:3.5",
          "pli": "vedanā … ",
          "en": "feeling … "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn12.28:3.6",
          "pli": "phasso … ",
          "en": "contact … "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn12.28:3.7",
          "pli": "saḷāyatanaṃ … ",
          "en": "the six sense fields … "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn12.28:3.8",
          "pli": "nāmarūpaṃ … ",
          "en": "name and form … "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn12.28:3.9",
          "pli": "viññāṇaṃ …. ",
          "en": "consciousness … "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn12.28:4.1",
          "pli": "Katame ca, bhikkhave, saṅkhārā? ",
          "en": "And what are choices? "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn12.28:4.2",
          "pli": "Tayome, bhikkhave, saṅkhārā—",
          "en": "There are three kinds of choices. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn12.28:4.3",
          "pli": "kāyasaṅkhāro, vacīsaṅkhāro, cittasaṅkhāro. ",
          "en": "Choices by way of body, speech, and mind. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn12.28:4.4",
          "pli": "Ime vuccanti, bhikkhave, saṅkhārā. ",
          "en": "These are called choices. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn12.28:4.5",
          "pli": "Avijjāsamudayā saṅkhārasamudayo; ",
          "en": "Ignorance is the origin of choices. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn12.28:4.6",
          "pli": "avijjānirodhā saṅkhāranirodho. ",
          "en": "When ignorance ceases, choices cease. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn12.28:4.7",
          "pli": "Ayameva ariyo aṭṭhaṅgiko maggo saṅkhāranirodhagāminī paṭipadā. ",
          "en": "The practice that leads to the cessation of choices is simply this noble eightfold path, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn12.28:4.8",
          "pli": "Seyyathidaṃ—sammādiṭṭhi … pe … sammāsamādhi. ",
          "en": "that is: right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, right effort, right mindfulness, and right immersion. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn12.28:5.1",
          "pli": "Yato kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu evaṃ jarāmaraṇaṃ pajānāti, evaṃ jarāmaraṇasamudayaṃ pajānāti, evaṃ jarāmaraṇanirodhaṃ pajānāti, evaṃ jarāmaraṇanirodhagāminiṃ paṭipadaṃ pajānāti, evaṃ jātiṃ pajānāti … pe … ",
          "en": "A mendicant understands old age and death, their origin, their cessation, and the practice that leads to their cessation. They understand rebirth … "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn12.28:5.2",
          "pli": "bhavaṃ … ",
          "en": "continued existence … "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn12.28:5.3",
          "pli": "upādānaṃ … ",
          "en": "grasping … "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn12.28:5.4",
          "pli": "taṇhaṃ … ",
          "en": "craving … "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn12.28:5.5",
          "pli": "vedanaṃ … ",
          "en": "feeling … "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn12.28:5.6",
          "pli": "phassaṃ … ",
          "en": "contact … "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn12.28:5.7",
          "pli": "saḷāyatanaṃ … ",
          "en": "the six sense fields … "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn12.28:5.8",
          "pli": "nāmarūpaṃ … ",
          "en": "name and form … "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn12.28:5.9",
          "pli": "viññāṇaṃ … ",
          "en": "consciousness … "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn12.28:5.10",
          "pli": "saṅkhāre … ",
          "en": "They understand choices, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn12.28:5.11",
          "pli": "saṅkhārasamudayaṃ … ",
          "en": "their origin, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn12.28:5.12",
          "pli": "saṅkhāranirodhaṃ … ",
          "en": "their cessation, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn12.28:5.13",
          "pli": "evaṃ saṅkhāranirodhagāminiṃ paṭipadaṃ pajānāti. ",
          "en": "and the practice that leads to their cessation. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn12.28:5.14",
          "pli": "Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, bhikkhu diṭṭhisampanno itipi, dassanasampanno itipi, āgato imaṃ saddhammaṃ itipi, passati imaṃ saddhammaṃ itipi, sekkhena ñāṇena samannāgato itipi, sekkhāya vijjāya samannāgato itipi, dhammasotaṃ samāpanno itipi, ariyo nibbedhikapañño itipi, amatadvāraṃ āhacca tiṭṭhati itipī”ti. ",
          "en": "Such a noble disciple is called ‘one accomplished in view’, ‘one accomplished in vision’, ‘one who has come to the true teaching’, ‘one who sees this true teaching’, ‘one endowed with a trainee’s knowledge’, ‘one who has entered the stream of the teaching’, ‘a noble one with penetrative wisdom’, and ‘one who stands pushing open the door of the deathless’.” "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn12.28:5.15",
          "pli": "Aṭṭhamaṃ. ",
          "en": ""
        }
      ],
